[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/weak_2s"]
[Student "S"]
{You have a good Weak 2-Bid but West already opened. So you just make a Weak Jump Overcall of 2\S. East passes and partner raises to 3\S. West passes.  

Pass. Partner is in charge. If he had wanted you to bid again he could have forced you with 2NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "W:96.984.AKQ874.72 T3.JT6.T96.KQJT9 A542.A52.J3.A865 KQJ87.KQ73.52.43"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
2D pass 2NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "12546e8d30ff12df9562e7d83150b93746248b687ee6a887ddecca33c63e5bce"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/weak_2s"]
[Student "S"]
{They shouldn't really be this easy. You bid 2NT and partner replies 3NT.  

You pass of course. Partner's 3NT says his suit is A K Q x x x and you can therefore count 9 top tricks.}

